      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RITZA OLD MATE (7) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.5 lengths at Warrnambool in a handy 22.02 beating Chalk And Cheese. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. LEKTRA BETA (4) goes very well at the course and distance with four wins and a placing from eight starts. Below best last time at this track (28.21) in a Grade 5 FIN, finishing a 13 length eighth. Makes strong appeal on best. KRAKEN TOMMY (2) quickly into stride to win over the 500m at Bendigo two runs back then raced on speed again when finishing third at this track last start. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from three starts. Expected to be in the finish again. AUSSIE WAGYU (3) was out of placings last time (23.28) at Geelong in a Mix 3/4, finishing seventh and beaten 10 lengths. Has already won out of this draw.",
